                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 881.00/624</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Blake</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-03T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1916, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>French Ambassador has sent Department text of declaration referring to abrogation
                    of capitulations in French zone of Morocco signed by all Powers signatory
                    Algeciras Conference and South American Republics. French Government desires the
                    United States use this text that uniformity may be maintained. Declaration is as
                    follows: [Follows text printed above:]</p>
                <p>Department desires your comments and suggestions this declaration, and also
                    whether Moroccan Government should be made party to treaty surrendering American
                    capitulatory rights French zone Morocco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
